net.openhft.fix.include.v42

Class FixMessageReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.openhft.fix.include.v42.FixMessageReader

  • public class FixMessageReader
extends Object
    This class is used for parsing a FIX 4.2 message. It follows a standard Fix4.2 protocol Field-specification that adheres to FixCommunity.org definition.

      • parseFixMsgBytes

        public void parseFixMsgBytes()
                      throws Exception
        Only support FIX 4.2 version. Parses fixMessage and return an array of Field objects. Precursor function to setFixBytes() else throws Exception A Field array index is defined by FixConstants.fieldsNumber As an example 
        Field fixField = Field[8];
 System.out.println("Fix Field Name:"+fixField.getName());
